&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experience and detail-oriented Warehouse Coordinator to support our medical device operations. This role&amp;nbsp;is responsible for&amp;nbsp;receiving, shipping, inventory&amp;nbsp;movement&amp;nbsp;and control all within&amp;nbsp;compliance ISO 13485 standards, and GMP requirements. The Warehouse Coordinator plays a key role in&amp;nbsp;maintaining inventory accuracy, product traceability, and supporting production and shipping activities. This is a full-time, hourly position, on-site in Alpharetta, GA Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inventory Management:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow all GMP, ISO 13485, and FDA 21 CFR Part 820 guidelines and company policies for material handling and storage.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support our inventory control specialist by performing cycle counts and physical inventory to ensure inventory accuracy.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage stock levels, reorder points, and restocking processes&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and package finished goods for distribution to our sterilization partner, 3PL, customers or intercompany ensuring proper documentation and labeling (e.g., lot numbers, part numbers, serial numbers, barcodes).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Warehouse Management:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Warehouse Management in Good Manufacturing Practice environment (GMP)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize and maintain the warehouse layout for optimal efficiency within a GMP environment.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track key performance indicators (KPIs) related to warehousing, including inbound receipts, internal on-time fill rates, truck&amp;nbsp;mileage.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately label,&amp;nbsp;store&amp;nbsp;and pick materials in designated areas according to company procedures, FIFO (First In, First Out)&amp;nbsp;or FEFO (First Expiry, First Out) principles.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clean and organized warehouse areas&amp;nbsp;in accordance with&amp;nbsp;6S standards.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shipping &amp;amp; Receiving:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
